axis: delimited-shift-reset
status: pending-runtime
needs: multi-prompt shift/reset on the portable VM (or the compiler-independent reference runner)
measured: `reset { 1 + shift { k => k(k(10)) } }` → `ssc: unbound global: reset` on
  portable-VM (ssc run --bytecode, 2026-07-14). The VM has effect/handle/resume but
  not delimited `shift`/`reset`.
expected: fresh/nested prompts with nearest-matching `reset`, same-prompt `shift`
  inside the shift body, and `shift` vs `shift0` distinction (core §4, §14.1). The
  compiler-independent Scala control local runner is the natural first home
  for these before any VM lowering.
